The paper deals with hypergraph partitioning, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of graph embeddings and machine learning techniques to improve the coarsening strategy suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the focus on performance optimization and numerical methods suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
